reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Super cute! Not heavy so it works well with layering. Very boxy fit but easy to match with jeans, sweats, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The sweater is well made. I love the deep rich color. The only thing is that is a little boxy fitting. It fits true to size. I am 5'3 at 143 pounds and got a medium. If you want a tighter fit size down as I could have gotten a small and would have fit as well. It's made to be oversized fit I believe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: A pretty sweater, but it catches on things and pulls too easily.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The fit is great definitely a thick sweater for warm weather

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not worth it
reviews.reviewText: Looks great online, but the second I tried it on I knew it was not for me. Looks like something more fit for a school boy than a 25 year old woman. Not at all flattering. The small was huge on me and the collar was so loose and awkward. Normally I like oversized sweaters but this one did not do it for me. Immediate return.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Warm and cozy. Oversized.
reviews.reviewText: This sweater is a chunky knit with a button up collar that lays wider than expected, but is very cute, soft and comfortable. It does run big or oversized. I normally wear a Large. This is a Medium and I could have worn a small in this sweater. I normally wear a Medium or Large in Prettygarden clothes. It is a warm sweater with a boxy style. It will not cover your hips, but it isn’t cropped. The Wine Red is a deep rich color like the sales page. Much prettier than my photos show. The color in the reflection in the round mirror is closest to the true color. It leans more toward Deep Rust than a purple Wine color. It didn’t bleed when hand washed, so I put it in a mesh bag and washed with some dark clothes, tumbled dry. Looks beautiful. For reference I am 5’3” tall, 150 pounds, 41-31-41. I have worn it several times, it looks good with jeans or skirts. I took it from the laundry basket to take photos so you can see how it fits. The arms are long on me so they should fit others well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute But Beware if You Have a Long Torso
reviews.reviewText: From my headline you can gather this top is a like but not love. As a tall woman (5'9" with a long torso, this top fell short, literally. It lays in an awkward cropped length that doesn't look purposeful but boxy & slightly awkward. I gave it to my daughter who is 4 inches shorter with a more average torso length and it looked great on her. I would say average height women will love this; tall ladies, beware.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This sweater is well made and very comfortable. It fits really well and I would buy in a different color. I like the chunky knit pattern to add some texture to the black and the thinner bottom hem means it doesn't get caught on pants like a wide hem can. Very warm for the winter!
